User Authentication:

Implement a user authentication system to allow users to register and log in.
Secure user data and ensure that each user can only access their own budgets.
Create Budget:

Allow users to create a new budget by specifying a name and potentially other details such as start date or duration.
Store the budget information in the database.
Manage Budget Categories:

Enable users to create multiple categories within each budget to track different types of expenses.
Implement functionality to add, edit, and delete budget categories.
Update the budget and category information in the database.
Track Expenses:

Provide a way for users to enter their expenses within each budget category.
Allow users to specify the amount, date, and category for each expense.
Update the total spent and remaining budget amounts for each category.
Visualization:

Implement visualizations such as charts or graphs to display spending patterns.
Generate visual representations of the budget categories and their respective spending amounts.
Provide an overview of the total spent and remaining budget for each category.
View and Manage Budgets:

Allow users to view a list of their budgets and navigate between them.
Provide options to edit or delete existing budgets.
Display the current status of each budget, including the total spent and remaining budget amount.
Responsive Design:

Ensure the application is responsive and works well on different devices and screen sizes.
Optimize the user interface for a seamless user experience across desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.